Afghanistan's Hamid Karzai to step down as president in 2014
Afghan President Hamid Karzai says his country will have a new leader in 2014, and thanks the US for helping to overthrow the Taliban. 10:09AM GMT 12 Jan 2013
"In a year and few months from today, I'll be a retired president," Karzai said during a speech at Georgetown University in Washington DC. He outlined a bright future for his country over the next ten years, pointing to improvements in education, infrastructure and security. He thanked the United States for its role in Afghanistan since overthrowing the Taliban in 2001. "Definitely Afghanistan will remember that it was the US assistance that brought so much to Afghanistan," Karzai said. "We will forget the less pleasant aspects of our relationship. We will move forward in the gratitude of the help that the United States has provided to Afghanistan and also our other neighbours."
