Wayne Rooney: England star player at World Cup 2010
Wayne Rooney: Profile of Wayne Rooney, England star player at World Cup 2010. Necessity: Wayne Rooney will prove an invaluable player for England in South Africa Photo: GETTY IMAGES	By Oliver Brown
8:20AM GMT 20 Nov 2009
Comments
Caps: 57
Goals: 25
World Cup appearances: 4 (2006)
World Cup 2010 qualification: 9 appearances/9 goals Club: Manchester United
Age: 24
Position: Striker Rooney is the one player England cannot do without on the high veld next summer. The distractions of being a new father should not count. His displays this season for Manchester United have been inspirational and his goals should prove the decisive factor if Fabio Capello's team are to reach the World Cup final at Johannesburg's Soccer City on July 11. Before Theo Walcott came on the scene, Rooney became the youngest player to play for England when he earned his first cap in a friendly against Australia on Feb 12, 2003, aged 17. Related Articles
England team at World Cup 2010
20 Nov 2009
His one World Cup to date, in 2006, brought only infamy, as he received a red card in England's quarter-final defeat to Portugal - an incident rendered all the more notorious by the sight of Ronaldo, Rooney's then United team-mate, winking at the Portugal bench. The chance for atonement, revenge - call it what you will - is nigh. England
